**My Analysis of Administrative Unit Changes**

My initial thought was to look at Province resolutions.  I found that "Tỉnh Phú Yên" was merged into "Tỉnh Đắk Lắk" based on the resolutions. This means I'm looking for changes in Đắk Lắk, not Phú Yên.

Then, I focused on other relevant resolutions. Resolution 1660/NQ-UBTVQH15, concerning Đắk Lắk, looks promising. Line 93 details that "phường Xuân Yên, phường Xuân Phú, xã Xuân Phương and xã Xuân Thịnh" form "phường Sông Cầu".  That lines up nicely with the old address mentioning "Thị xã Sông Cầu".

I verified the new ward information. I found a match in the new wards list for "Xã Xuân Cảnh" within "Tỉnh Đắk Lắk". This strongly suggests that "Xã Xuân Bình" is now part of the new ward, "Xã Xuân Cảnh". The reference of "Thị xã Sông Cầu" in the old address seems contextual.
